CHAP. XXX. For we invoke on behalf of the safety of the emperors a God who is everlasting, a God who is real, a God who is living, whom even the emperors themselves prefer should be propitious to them beyond all others. They know who gave them empire, they know, as human beings, who gave them life also, they feel that he is the only God, irs whose power alone they are, to whom they are second, after whom they are first, before all and above all gods. Why not? since they are above all men, who of course are alive and take precedence 01 the dead.
